Appends the specified calling convention to this dictionary.

No check is made for whether the calling convention is already present in the dictionary--it is added regardless.

const Convention* BinaryCallingConvention::find ( size_t  wordsize,
const std::string &  name,
size_t *  start_at = NULL 
)

Finds a calling convention.

The dictionary is scanned to find a calling convention having the specified name and wordsize. If the specified wordsize is zero then wordsize is not considered when searching. An optional start_at value can be specified, in which case the search starts at the specified index in the dictionary and returns the index at which the matching calling convention was found (or the dictionary size when no match was found). Returns a pointer to a matching calling convention, or the null pointer if no match was found.
